@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
    var product = (string)(ViewBag.ProductName ?? "BareProx");
    var contact = (string)(ViewBag.ContactEmail ?? "[nwtobbe@gmail.com](mailto:nwtobbe@gmail.com)");
}

<style>
    .policy h2 {
        margin-top: 1.25rem;
    }

    .policy h3 {
        margin-top: 1rem;
    }

    .policy code {
        padding: .15rem .35rem;
        background: rgba(0,0,0,.05);
        border-radius: .25rem;
    }
</style>

<div class="policy">
    <h1 class="mb-3">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p><em>Last updated: 2026-03-27 UTC</em></p>

    ```
    <p>
        This Privacy Policy describes how <strong>@product</strong> processes data when you use the application.
        @product is self-hosted software, meaning it is deployed, configured, and operated by you.
    </p>

    <h2>Data Controller</h2>
    <p>
        The operator of the @product installation is the data controller and is responsible for compliance with applicable
        data protection laws (such as GDPR). The developer of @product does not have access to or process any data
        from your installation.
    </p>

    <h2>What @product Stores</h2>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Configuration data:</strong> Proxmox and NetApp connection details, settings, and schedules.</li>
        <li><strong>Operational logs:</strong> Job history (backups, restores), warnings/errors, timestamps, and related metadata.</li>
        <li><strong>User accounts:</strong> Authentication and authorization data via ASP.NET Identity (if enabled).</li>
        <li><strong>Notifications:</strong> Email settings and recipients if email notifications are configured.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>What @product Does Not Do</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>No built-in analytics or tracking.</li>
        <li>No telemetry or usage data is sent to the developer unless explicitly configured by you.</li>
        <li>No automatic data sharing with third parties.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Cookies</h2>
    <p>
        @product may use cookies for authentication and session management. These cookies are strictly necessary
        for the application to function. Anti-forgery tokens (enabled by default) may also use cookies to protect
        against cross-site request forgery (CSRF).
    </p>

    <h2>Log & Diagnostic Data</h2>
    <p>
        Application and job logs are stored locally (e.g., in a database or log files). You control retention and access.
        Logs may include VM names, storage identifiers, cluster/host names, timestamps, and error details.
    </p>

    <h2>Security</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Credentials and secrets should be stored encrypted at rest (e.g., using Data Protection APIs or a key vault).</li>
        <li>Self-signed certificates may be generated in-app; using trusted certificates in production is recommended.</li>
        <li>Access to the management interface and APIs should be restricted to trusted networks and users.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Data Export & Deletion</h2>
    <p>
        As the operator, you control all stored data. You may export or delete data using your database or storage tools.
        For user-related data requests, follow your organization’s policies and applicable legal requirements.
    </p>

    <h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
    <p>
        Optional features may connect to external services (for example, update checks, package repositories,
        or configured email servers). These connections are initiated and controlled by your configuration.
    </p>

    <h2>Legal Basis</h2>
    <p>
        As a self-hosted application, @product processes data according to your configuration and usage.
        The legal basis for processing (such as legitimate interest, contractual necessity, or consent)
        is determined by the operator of the system.
    </p>

    <h2>Remote Access</h2>
    <p>
        @product does not include any remote access, telemetry, or backdoor functionality.
        All data remains within your environment unless you explicitly configure external integrations.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
        For questions about the software, contact: <a href="mailto:@contact">@contact</a>.<br />
        For questions regarding data processed by your installation, contact your system administrator.
    </p>

    <hr />
    <small class="text-muted">
        @product is licensed under the GNU Affero General Public License v3.0 (AGPL-3.0).
        You are responsible for operating and configuring the software in compliance with applicable laws and policies.
    </small>
    ```

</div>
